cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with word transductions, which are a fundamental concept in automata theory. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper proposes a logical formalism for describing a class of resynchronizations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the complexity of the equivalence and containment problems for two-way word transducers. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also possible as the paper proves the PSPACE-completeness of the equivalence and containment problems. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the semantics of word transductions.
